_id":"U_kgDODx9_MQ","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/253722417?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Erick52106","html_url":"https://github.com/Erick52106","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Erick52106/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Erick52106/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Erick52106/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Erick52106/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Erick52106/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Erick52106/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Erick52106/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Erick52106/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Erick52106/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"open_issues":0,"closed_issues":21,"state":"open","created_at":"2026-05-02T19:49:41Z","updated_at":"2026-05-13T22:28:47Z","due_on":null,"closed_at":null},"comments":2,"created_at":"2026-05-09T18:17:28Z","updated_at":"2026-05-13T22:17:58Z","closed_at":"2026-05-13T22:17:24Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Purpose\n\nThis issue defines and runs the third read-only brownfield dogfood evidence gate required by #222.\n\nThe goal is to increase 4.7 readiness confidence by testing `spec-injector` against a third public, non-sensitive, non-`spec-injector`, non-`tachigo` brownfield target under strict read-only constraints.\n\nThis is not a runtime implementation issue.\n\n## Parent / source decision\n\nParent planning issue:\n- #222\n\nDecision draft:\n- https://github.com/Erick52106/spec-injector/issues/222#issuecomment-4413284193\n\nImportant decision:\nThird dogfood is the primary next 4.7 evidence gate, but not sufficient by itself. #206, Layer 3, Layer 4, and README / visual overclaim gates still need written decisions before any runtime-adjacent work starts.\n\n## Scope\n\nThis issue should produce a third dogfood report that includes:\n\n1. Target selection\n   - public / non-sensitive repo\n   - not `spec-injector`\n   - not `tachigo`\n   - not `tachiya`\n   - not `storefront`\n   - different enough from previous dogfood targets\n   - pinned target commit SHA\n   - clear target issue / request source\n\n2. Read-only safety\n   - no `spec init`\n   - no `.spec-injector/` creation in target repo\n   - no target repo branch\n   - no target repo commit\n   - no target repo PR\n   - no target repo file changes\n   - no target repo cleanup / reset / stash / clean\n   - no sensitive source copied into report\n\n3. Dogfood execution\n   - use `spec plan` / dry-run style command\n   - prefer external config or safe fixture config\n   - capture command, exit code, stdout/stderr summary, and important diagnostics\n   - do not mutate target repo\n\n4. Evidence analysis\n   - source reference precision\n   - diagnostics visibility\n   - missing / unreadable / read-failed / alias / truncation behavior\n   - classifier true positives / false positives / false negatives\n   - monorepo or path-shape friction, if present\n   - README claim impact\n   - #206 relation, if any\n   - Layer 3 relation, if any\n   - Layer 4 relation, if any\n\n5. Verdict\n   - PASS / WARN / FAIL\n   - rationale\n   - what this means for 4.7 readiness\n\n## Target selection criteria\n\nA valid target must be:\n\n- Public or otherwise safe to describe without leaking private code.\n- Non-sensitive.\n- Brownfield: has existing issues, docs, and source structure.\n- Different from prior dogfood examples.\n- Reproducible through pinned target commit SHA.\n- Usable under read-only constraints.\n\nForbidden targets:\n\n- `Erick52106/spec-injector`\n- `tachigo`\n- `tachiya`\n- `storefront`\n- Any private or sensitive repo\n- Any target requiring branch / commit / PR / file mutation\n- Any target requiring secrets or private credentials\n\n## Required report format\n\nThe final dogfood report should include:\n\n| Section | Required content |\n|---|---|\n| Target | repo URL, pinned commit SHA, issue/request source |\n| Target selection rationale | why this repo/issue improves target diversity |\n| Safety checklist | read-only confirmations and mutation-prevention checks |\n| Commands run | exact commands, cwd, config strategy |\n| Input summary | issue/request summary and selected docs/source strategy |\n| Output summary | useful context, diagnostics, warnings, exit code |\n| Source reference precision | true positives / false positives / false negatives |\n| Diagnostics quality | missing / unreadable / read-failed / alias / truncation behavior |\n| Classifier assessment | domain signal quality and failure modes |\n| Monorepo/path friction | if applicable |\n| README claim impact | what current README claims are supported or caveated |\n| #206 relation | whether this provides zh-TW evidence; likely no unless target uses zh-TW |\n| Layer 3 relation | protocol/catalog implications |\n| Layer 4 relation | visual/status/companion implications without runtime claim |\n| Verdict | PASS / WARN / FAIL with rationale |\n| Follow-up recommendations | issues that should or should not be opened |\n\n## PASS / WARN / FAIL interpretation\n\nPASS:\n- read-only flow produces useful bounded task context\n- diagnostics are visible\n- no target repo mutation\n- no major misleading source references\n- no README claim is contradicted\n\nWARN:\n- output is useful but has caveats\n- false positives / false negatives exist but are explainable\n- monorepo/path-shape friction appears\n- diagnostics or classifier behavior needs follow-up\n- README claims remain valid only with caveats\n\nFAIL:\n- flow produces misleading context\n- diagnostics hide importan