otal_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## CVE\n- **ID:** CVE-2026-44459\n- **Package:** `hono@4.12.16` → fix at `hono@4.12.18`\n- **Severity:** LOW\n- **Vulnerability class:** Improper Input Validation (CWE-20) — `hono/utils/jwt` `verify()` mis-handles non-spec NumericDate claims (`exp`, `nbf`, `iat`)\n- **GHSA:** GHSA-hm8q-7f3q-5f36\n- **Transitivity:** transitive — both lockfiles\n\n## Locations\n- `package-lock.json:13393`\n- `mcp-docs/package-lock.json:2225`\n\n## Summary\nThe JWT validation routine in `hono/utils/jwt` combined option, presence, and threshold checks in a short-circuiting expression. As a result, a falsy numeric value short-circuited the presence check, non-finite numerics compared as never-after-now / never-expired, and non-numeric types produced NaN comparisons evaluating false. This deviates from RFC 7519 §4.1.4, which requires NumericDate to be a finite JSON numeric. An actor able to issue tokens accepted by the application (with access to the signing key) could craft tokens whose `exp`, `nbf`, or `iat` silently bypass time-based enforcement. Deployments with a well-formed token issuer and protected signing key are not affected — exploitation requires either the issuer issuing malformed tokens or signing-key compromise.\n\n## Reachability\n**Reachability assessment: not reachable.** Compendiq's JWT layer uses `jose` (`backend/src/core/plugins/auth.ts:3` — `import * as jose from 'jose'`), not Hono. `jose.jwtVerify()` (line 97) enforces RFC-compliant NumericDate handling. No code imports `hono/utils/jwt`. Hono is transitive only via `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk → @hono/node-server`, and the MCP SDK does not use Hono's JWT helpers.\n\n## Proposed remediation\nBump root `overrides` to `^4.12.18`:\n\n```json\n\"overrides\": {\n  \"hono\": \"^4.12.18\"\n}\n```\n\nmcp-docs has its own lockfile — add an override entry or run `npm install` from `mcp-docs/`.\n\n## Related CVEs\n- CVE-2026-44455 (#642 — JSX tag injection, fix at 4.12.16)\n- CVE-2026-44456 (#643 — bodyLimit bypass, fix at 4.12.16)\n- CVE-2026-44457 (#644 — cache leak, fix at 4.12.18)\n- CVE-2026-44458 (#645 — JSX style CSS injection, fix at 4.12.18)\n\nAll five hono advisories closed by `hono@^4.12.18`.\n\n## References\n- GHSA: https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-hm8q-7f3q-5f36\n- Advisory: https://github.com/honojs/hono/security/advisories/GHSA-hm8q-7f3q-5f36\n\n---\n_Filed by automated Semgrep triage. Source: Semgrep cloud SCA scan._","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/issues/646/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/issues/646/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/issues/643","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/issues/643/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/issues/643/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/issues/643/events","html_url":"https://github.com/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/issues/643","id":4444644211,"node_id":"I_kwDORyqgoc8AAAABCOvjcw","number":643,"title":"chore(deps): CVE-2026-44456 — bump hono to 4.12.16 (bodyLimit bypass)","user":{"login":"laboef1900","id":12890239,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyODkwMjM5","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/12890239?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/laboef1900","html_url":"https://github.com/laboef1900","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/laboef1900/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/laboef1900/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/laboef1900/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/laboef1900/sta