ransfer-Encoding: chunked`). The middleware wraps the body in a stream that counts bytes asynchronously and runs the handler before the size decision is final, then retrofits a `413` only by checking `c.error` afterward. Oversized chunked requests can therefore reach handler logic and return `200` instead of `413` when the handler doesn't read the body, reads only the first chunks, or swallows the read error.\n\n## Reachability\n**Reachability assessment: not reachable.** Compendiq's HTTP servers are Fastify (backend) and Express (mcp-docs); neither uses Hono's `bodyLimit()` middleware. Hono is purely transitive via `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk → @hono/node-server`. The MCP SDK uses Hono internally only for the Streamable HTTP transport server adapter (`@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/streamableHttp.js`) and does not invoke `bodyLimit()`. We enforce request size limits at the Fastify layer (`bodyLimit` option on the Fastify instance) — see `backend/src/server.ts` — and via nginx in front of the frontend container (`frontend/nginx.conf`). No code path in CE relies on Hono's `bodyLimit()`.\n\n## Proposed remediation\nSame fix as the other hono CVEs — bump the root `overrides` entry to `^4.12.18` to remediate all five hono advisories at once.\n\n```json\n\"overrides\": {\n  \"hono\": \"^4.12.18\"\n}\n```\n\nmcp-docs has its own lockfile; either add an `overrides` block to `mcp-docs/package.json` or run `npm install` inside `mcp-docs/`.\n\n## Related CVEs\n- CVE-2026-44455 (#642 — JSX tag injection, fix at 4.12.16)\n- CVE-2026-44457 (cache leak, fix at 4.12.18)\n- CVE-2026-44458 (CSS injection, fix at 4.12.18)\n- CVE-2026-44459 (JWT NumericDate, fix at 4.12.18)\n\nA single bump to `hono@^4.12.18` closes all five.\n\n## References\n- GHSA: https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-9vqf-7f2p-gf9v\n- Advisory: https://github.com/honojs/hono/security/advisories/GHSA-9vqf-7f2p-gf9v\n\n---\n_Filed by automated Semgrep triage. Source: Semgrep cloud SCA scan._","reactions":{"url":"http