,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/labels/security","name":"security","color":"B60205","default":false,"description":"Security-related issues"},{"id":10627238917,"node_id":"LA_kwDORyqgoc8AAAACeW7MBQ","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/labels/dependencies","name":"dependencies","color":"0366d6","default":false,"description":"Pull requests that update a dependency file"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-05-14T09:05:42Z","updated_at":"2026-05-14T17:09:39Z","closed_at":"2026-05-14T17:09:39Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## CVE\n- **ID:** CVE-2026-44455\n- **Package:** `hono@4.12.14` → fix at `hono@4.12.16`\n- **Severity:** MODERATE\n- **Vulnerability class:** CWE-79 — HTML Injection via unvalidated JSX tag names in `hono/jsx` SSR\n- **GHSA:** GHSA-69xw-7hcm-h432\n- **Transitivity:** transitive — only the mcp-docs lockfile is on the vulnerable line; CE root already overrides hono to `^4.12.14` (in root `package.json`, line 33) and resolves to `4.12.16` via `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk@1.29.0 → @hono/node-server@1.19.14 → hono` plus the override\n\n## Locations\n- `mcp-docs/package-lock.json:2225` (root `package-lock.json` is on 4.12.16 via the override, so this CVE is already addressed there)\n\n## Summary\nWhen rendering JSX elements to HTML strings in `hono/jsx`, attribute values were escaped and attribute names were validated, but element tag names were inserted into the output without validation. If untrusted input is used as a tag name via programmatic `jsx()` or `createElement()` APIs during SSR, characters such as `<`, `>`, quotes, or whitespace can break out of the intended element and introduce unintended HTML, attributes, or event handlers — potentially leading to XSS.\n\n## Reachability\n**Reachability assessment: not reachable.** mcp-docs does not use `hono/jsx` or any JSX SSR — it is an Express application (`mcp-docs/src/index.ts:11` `import express from 'express'`) that hosts an MCP Streamable HTTP transport. The hono dependency is purely transitive via `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk → @hono/node-server`, and the SDK itself does not use the JSX renderer. No code in `backend/src`, `frontend/src`, or `mcp-docs/src` imports `hono/jsx`, calls `jsx()`, or calls `createElement()` from hono. CE root already runs the patched `4.12.16` via the existing override; mcp-docs lockfile is still on `4.12.14`.\n\n## Proposed remediation\nBump the root `overrides` entry (currently `^4.12.14`) to `^4.12.18` (which also remediates the related companion CVEs in one go — see Related CVEs below). The mcp-docs workspace has its own lockfile; either add an `overrides` block to `mcp-docs/package.json` or run `npm install` from `mcp-docs/` after upstream is bumped.\n\n```json\n\"overrides\": {\n  \"hono\": \"^4.12.18\"\n}\n```\n\n## Related CVEs\n- CVE-2026-44456 (hono bodyLimit bypass, fix at 4.12.16) — also fixed by the same bump.\n- CVE-2026-44457 (hono cache leak, fix at 4.12.18)\n- CVE-2026-44458 (hono CSS injection in JSX, fix at 4.12.18)\n- CVE-2026-44459 (hono JWT NumericDate validation, fix at 4.12.18)\n\nA single bump to `hono@^4.12.18` closes all five hono CVEs.\n\n## References\n- GHSA: https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-69xw-7hcm-h432\n- Advisory: https://github.com/honojs/hono/security/advisories/GHSA-69xw-7hcm-h432\n\n---\n_Filed by automated Semgrep triage. Source: Semgrep cloud SCA scan._","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/issues/642/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/issues/642/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/issues/644","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/issues/644/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/issues/644/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/issues/644/events","html_url":"https://github.com/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/issues/644","id":4444646252,"node_id":"I_kwDORyqgoc8AAAABCOvrbA","number":644,"title":"chore(deps): CVE-2026-44457 — bump hono to 4.12.18 (cache leak)","user":{"login":"laboef1900","id":12890239,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyODkwMjM5","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/12890239?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/laboef1900","html_url":"https://github.com/laboef1900","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/laboef1900/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/laboef1900/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/laboef1900/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/laboef1900/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/laboef1900/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/laboef1900/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/laboef1900/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/laboef1900/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/laboef1900/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":10595087375,"node_id":"LA_kwDORyqgoc8AAAACd4Q0Dw","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/labels/security","name":"security","color":"B60205","default":false,"description":"Security-related issues"},{"id":10627238917,"node_id":"LA_kwDORyqgoc8AAAACeW7MBQ","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/labels/dependencies","name":"dependencies","color":"0366d6","default":false,"description":"Pull requests that update a dependency file"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-05-14T09:06:17Z","updated_at":"2026-05-14T17:09:40Z","closed_at":"2026-05-14T17:09:40Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## CVE\n- **ID:** CVE-2026-44457\n- **Package:** `hono@4.12.16` → fix at `hono@4.12.18`\n- **Severity:** MODERATE\n- **Vulnerability class:** Information Exposure via Cache (CWE-525) — Cache Middleware ignores `Vary: Authorization` / `Vary: Cookie`\n- **GHSA:** GHSA-p77w-8qqv-26rm\n- **Transitivity:** transitive — both lockfiles. CE root is already on `4.12.16` via the `^4.12.14` override; mcp-docs is on `4.12.14`. Both need the bump.\n\n## Locations\n- `package-lock.json:13393`\n- `mcp-docs/package-lock.json:2225`\n\n## Summary\nHono's Cache Middleware skips caching for `Vary: *`, `Cache-Control: private|no-store|no-cache`, and `Set-Cookie`, but does not treat `Vary: Authorization` or `Vary: Cookie` — the standard RFC 9110/9111 signals for per-user responses — as cache-skip reasons. As a result, a response cached for one authenticated user may be served to subsequent requests from different users when applications rely on `Vary: Authorization` or `Vary: Cookie` to scope responses without also setting `Cache-Control: private`.\n\n## Reachability\n**Reachability assessment: not reachable.** Compendiq does not use Hono's Cache Middleware. The backend is Fastify; mcp-docs is Express. Hono enters the dependency tree only via `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk → @hono/node-server`, which does not register Cache Middleware. Our caching layers (Redis via `LLM_CACHE_TTL`, the LLM-response cache in `backend/src/domains/llm/services/llm-cache.ts`, and the mcp-docs Redis cache in `mcp-docs/src/cache/redis-cache.ts`) are application-level and key on (user_id, content_hash) — they are not affected by Hono's Cache Middleware bug.\n\n## Proposed remediation\nBump the root `overrides` entry to `^4.12.18` (also remediates CVE-2026-44458 and CVE-2026-44459 in one step). The mcp-docs workspace has its own lockfile — add an `overrides` block or run `npm install` from `mcp-docs/`.\n\n```json\n\"overrides\": {\n  \"hono\": \"^4.12.18\"\n}\n```\n\n## Related CVEs\n- CVE-2026-44455 (#642 — JSX tag injection, fix at 4.12.16)\n- CVE-2026-44456 (#643 — bodyLimit bypass, fix at 4.12.16)\n- CVE-2026-44458 (CSS declaration injection in JSX `style`, fix at 4.12.18)\n- CVE-2026-44459 (JWT NumericDate validation, fix at 4.12.18)\n\nAll five remediated by `hono@^4.12.18`.\n\n## References\n- GHSA: https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-p77w-8qqv-26rm\n- Advisory: https://github.com/honojs/hono/security/advisories/GHSA-p77w-8qqv-26rm\n\n---\n_Filed by automated Semgrep triage. Source: Semgrep cloud SCA scan._","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/issues/644/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Compendiq/compendiq-ce/issues/644/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/node-server/issues/353","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/node-server","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/node-server/issues/353/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/node-server/issues/353/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/node-server/issues/353/events","html_url":"https://github.com/honojs/node-server/issues/353","id":4442550642,"node_id":"I_kwDOH-h1q88AAAABCMvxcg","number":353,"title":"Public declaration files reference undeclared dependency `ws`","user":{"login":"heroboy","id":54468,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU0NDY4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/54468?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/heroboy","html_url":"https://github.com/heroboy","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/heroboy/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/heroboy/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/heroboy/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/heroboy/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/heroboy/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/heroboy/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/heroboy/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/heroboy/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/heroboy/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":9,"created_at":"2026-05-14T02:12:08Z","updated_at":"2026-05-24T08:17:37Z","closed_at":"2026-05-24T08:17:37Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"`@hono/node-server` exposes `ws` in its public declaration files, but `ws` is not declared as a dependency.\n\nFor example, `dist/index.d.mts` contains:\n\n```ts\nimport { WebSocket, WebSocketServer } from \"ws\";\n```\n\nHowever, `ws` is currently only a `devDependency`.\n\nThis causes TypeScript consumers to fail compilation with:\n\n```txt\nTS2307: Cannot find module 'ws' or its corresponding type declarations.\n```\n\nThis is reproducible under pnpm / NodeNext module resolution, but the issue is not pnpm-specific — consumers are not expected to install a package's `devDependencies`.\n\nSince `ws` is referenced from public `.d.ts/.d.mts` files, it is effectively part of the package's public type surface and should probably be declared as one of:\n\n* `dependencies`\n* `peerDependencies`\n* optional peer dependency\n\nOtherwise consumers must manually install `ws` (and sometimes `@types/ws`) even if they do not use websocket functionality directly.\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/node-server/issues/353/reactions","total_count":2,"+1":2,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/node-server/issues/353/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/hono/issues/4920","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/hono","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/hono/issues/4920/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/hono/issues/4920/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/hono/issues/4920/events","html_url":"https://github.com/honojs/hono/issues/4920","id":4419564783,"node_id":"I_kwDOGiE5WM8AAAABB2007w","number":4920,"title":"Add the bytes() method to HonoRequest.","user":{"login":"pom3333","id":145071566,"node_id":"U_kgDOCKWdzg","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/145071566?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/pom3333","html_url":"https://github.com/pom3333","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pom3333/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pom3333/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pom3333/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pom3333/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pom3333/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/us