s.com/package/@clerk/backend\n- https://github.com/honojs/middleware/blob/a6f4ef54313978f82e7f68af84846672cc2b5179/packages/clerk-auth/package.json#L45\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/middleware/issues/1833/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/middleware/issues/1833/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/PerryTS/perry/issues/421","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/PerryTS/perry","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/PerryTS/perry/issues/421/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/PerryTS/perry/issues/421/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/PerryTS/perry/issues/421/events","html_url":"https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/421","id":4367719528,"node_id":"I_kwDOQ8nqJM8AAAABBFYcaA","number":421,"title":"Compile `hono` end-to-end via `perry.compilePackages`","user":{"login":"proggeramlug","id":8865968,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg4NjU5Njg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/8865968?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/proggeramlug","html_url":"https://github.com/proggeramlug","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/proggeramlug/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/proggeramlug/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/proggeramlug/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/proggeramlug/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/proggeramlug/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/proggeramlug/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/proggeramlug/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/proggeramlug/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/proggeramlug/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":2,"created_at":"2026-05-02T03:14:09Z","updated_at":"2026-05-06T20:07:19Z","closed_at":"2026-05-06T20:07:19Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"Tracking issue for landing **`hono`** (https://github.com/honojs/hono) as a `perry.compilePackages` target.\n\nSurfaced from a Medusa-vs-Perry compatibility study. Takeaway: a faithful `express` shim is a tarpit — Express's value is the prototype-mutation contract that ~200 widely-used middlewares depend on, which is fundamentally AOT-hostile. Hono is the modern, actively-maintained, AOT-friendly Express-shaped framework — same design lineage as Drizzle, built for Workers/Bun/Deno and the same constraints Perry has.\n\n## Why Hono (vs. an Express shim)\n\n- **Express-shaped API** — `app.get('/', c => c.json({...}))` is instantly familiar to Express users.\n- **No prototype mutation** — Express extends `req`/`res` prototypes at boot; Hono's `Context` is a plain object built per request. AOT-natural.\n- **No `req.app` circularity** — clean dependency direction, no runtime metaprogramming required.\n- **Trie-based router** — fast, no runtime regex compilation.\n- **Middleware contract is a clean async function** `(c, next) => {...}` — composes statically, no side-effects-on-shared-prototypes.\n- **Built for portable runtimes from day one** — Workers, Bun, Deno, Node, edge. Same constraint set as Perry.\n- **Growing fast** — 20K+ stars, increasingly the default for new TS backends.\n\nPerry already ships **`fastify`** in `perry-stdlib`. Hono complements it: Fastify is the higher-throughput plugin-driven choice; Hono is the lighter Express-shaped choice with the strongest edge-runtime fit. The two together cover most of the modern TS backend space. **A full Express shim is explicitly out of scope** (see below).\n\n## Scope\n\nEnd-to-end means: user does `npm install hono`, adds `\"compilePackages\": [\"hono\"]` to `package.json`, writes a standard Hono program with routing + a couple middleware + JSON request/response, runs `perry compile app.ts -o app && ./app`, and gets a single-file native binary serving HTTP.\n\nLikely shake-out areas:\n\n1. **`hono` source compilation** — pure TS, no native bindings. Designed for portable runtimes, so most should compile out of the box. Standard `compilePackages` shake-out for any TS-subset features individual modules trip over (same shape as #348).\n2. **Adapter** — Hono uses runtime adapters (`@hono/node-server`, Bun adapter, Deno adapter, Workers adapter). Perry needs a server adapter that hands the listening socket / request stream to Hono's `app.fetch`. Most natural: build on top of Perry's existing `http` / `fastify` plumbing in `perry-stdlib` to provide a `@hono/perry-server` shape.\n3. **Middleware ecosystem** — Hono ships official middlewares (`hono/cors`, `hono/jwt`, `hono/logger`, etc.) under its own namespace, all pure TS. These should fall out of (1) for free.\n4. **Web Standards APIs Hono leans on** — `Request`/`Response`/`Headers`/`URL`/`URLSearchParams`. Verify Perry's coverage matches what Hono uses; gaps land here as sub-issues.\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- A 30-line Hono program (routing + JSON request/response + one middleware — e.g. a logger or a basic auth header check) compiles via `perry compile`, produces a single-file native binary, serves real HTTP traffic, and matches the same program under `node --experimental-strip-types` byte-for-byte for response bodies/headers.\n- At least one official Hono middleware (`hono/cors` or `hono/logger`) verified end-to-end.\n- Whatever shake-out fixes are needed in `perry-codegen` / `perry-stdlib` to make the dependency tree compile cleanly, land them under this umbrella.\n- A `@hono/perry-server`-shaped adapter exists, either inside `perry-stdlib` or as a separate package, and is documented.\n\n## Out of scope (separate follow-ups)\n\n- A full Express compatibility shim. Express's middleware ecosystem assumes prototype mutation; faithful support is ~20kloc of Rust to track upstream forever, and a partial shim is worse than no shim (\"Express-but-not-really\" is confusing). The express story becomes \"use Hono or Fastify; here's a migration guide.\"\n- A *minimal* Express subset module (`app.get/use/listen` + `req.params/query/body` + `res.json/send/status` only, scoped to tutorial-grade apps) is **possibly** worth a separate small issue, *only* if real demand emerges. Default position: skip.\n- Elysia / itty-router / other small frameworks — separate tracking issues if/when demand materializes.\n\n## Strategic context\n\nCompanion to a Drizzle `compilePackages` tracking issue (filed alongside this one). Together they cover the modern AOT-friendly TS backend stack — the same selection Workers/Bun/Deno users have converged on for the same reasons Perry has. The thesis is: align with the modern-edge-TS lineage (Hono/Drizzle/Zod/Valibot) rather than chasing legacy-Node compat (Express/MikroORM/Awilix/NestJS).","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/PerryTS/perry/issues/421/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/PerryTS/perry/issues/421/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Soontao/presentations/issues/650","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Soontao/presentations","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Soontao/presentations/issues/650/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Soontao/presentations/issues/650/comments",