n\n###  Vulnerability Details\n<p>  \n  \najv (Another JSON Schema Validator) before 8.18.0 is vulnerable to Regular Expression Denial of Service (ReDoS) when the $data option is enabled. The pattern keyword accepts runtime data via JSON Pointer syntax ($data reference), which is passed directly to the JavaScript RegExp() constructor without validation. An attacker can inject a malicious regex pattern (e.g., \"^(a|a)*$\") combined with crafted input to cause catastrophic backtracking. A 31-character payload causes approximately 44 seconds of CPU blocking, with each additional character doubling execution time. This enables complete denial of service with a single HTTP request against any API using ajv with $data: true for dynamic schema validation. This issue is also fixed in version 6.14.0.\n\n<p>Publish Date: 2026-02-11\n<p>URL: <a href=https://www.mend.io/vulnerability-database/CVE-2025-69873>CVE-2025-69873</a></p>\n</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n###  CVSS 3 Score Details (<b>2.9</b>)\n<p>\n\nBase Score Metrics:\n- Exploitability Metrics:\n  - Attack Vector: Local\n  - Attack Complexity: High\n  - Privileges Required: None\n  - User Interaction: None\n  - Scope: Unchanged\n- Impact Metrics:\n  - Confidentiality Impact: None\n  - Integrity Impact: None\n  - Availability Impact: Low\n</p>\nFor more information on CVSS3 Scores, click <a href=\"https://www.first.org/cvss/calculator/3.0\">here</a>.\n</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n###  Suggested Fix\n<p>\n\n<p>Type: Upgrade version</p>\n<p>Origin: <a href=\"https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-2g4f-4pwh-qvx6\">https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-2g4f-4pwh-qvx6</a></p>\n<p>Release Date: 2026-02-11</p>\n<p>Fix Resolution: https://github.com/ajv-validator/ajv.git - v8.18.0,https://github.com/ajv-validator/ajv.git - v6.14.0</p>\n\n</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n\nStep up your Open Source Security Game with Mend [here](https://www.whitesourcesoftware.com/full_solution_bolt_github)\n</details>","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Soontao/presentations/issues/650/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Soontao/presentations/issues/650/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/PerryTS/perry/issues/577","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/PerryTS/perry","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/PerryTS/perry/issues/577/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/PerryTS/perry/issues/577/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/PerryTS/perry/issues/577/events","html_url":"https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/577","id":4404991785,"node_id":"I_kwDOQ8nqJM8AAAABBo7XKQ","number":577,"title":"Implement node:http / node:https / node:http2 + WebSocket upgrade for npm-ecosystem HTTP server compat","user":{"login":"proggeramlug","id":8865968,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg4NjU5Njg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/8865968?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/proggeramlug","html_url":"https://github.com/proggeramlug","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/proggeramlug/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/proggeramlug/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/proggeramlug/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/proggeramlug/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/proggeramlug/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/proggeramlug/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/proggeramlug/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/proggeramlug/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/proggeramlug/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2026-05-08T08:31:30Z","updated_at":"2026-05-08T13:21:11Z","closed_at":"2026-05-08T13:20:14Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Goal\n\nImplement a faithful subset of Node.js's `node:http`, `node:https`, and `node:http2` modules (server side) plus WebSocket upgrade integration, so that perry-compiled programs can run unmodified Node HTTP frameworks as long-lived servers. Closes #487 as a side effect; primary scope is broader compat.\n\n## Why\n\nHono is the immediate trigger (#421/#487), but every Node-ecosystem HTTP framework — Express, Koa, Fastify, Polka, h3, Hapi, Restify, NestJS adapters — depends on `node:http` directly or through a single thin adapter. Today perry has hyper plumbing in `perry-stdlib::framework::server` and `perry-ext-fastify`, but neither exposes the standard Node module shape. Users wanting to deploy a perry-compiled server have to write boilerplate or pick the one framework with native bindings (currently fastify).\n\nImplementing `node:http` correctly unlocks ALL of these in one shot. The `@hono/node-server` package is ~200 lines of TS and works unchanged against any compliant `node:http` host.\n\n## Scope\n\n### Phase 1 — `node:http` server (MVP)\n\nThe minimum surface required for `@hono/node-server` + Express + Koa + Polka to work for GET/POST/JSON workloads:\n\n- \\`http.createServer(handler)\\` returning a \\`Server\\`\n- \\`Server.listen(port, hostname?, backlog?, cb?)\\` with all overload shapes\n- \\`Server.address()\\` returning \\`{ port, address, family }\\`\n- \\`Server.close(cb?)\\`, \\`Server.closeAllConnections()\\`, \\`Server.closeIdleConnections()\\`\n- \\`Server.on('request' | 'connection' | 'close' | 'listening' | 'error', listener)\\`\n- \\`IncomingMessage\\` (Readable stream):\n  - \\`.method\\`, \\`.url\\`, \\`.headers\\`, \\`.rawHeaders\\`, \\`.httpVersion\\`, \\`.complete\\`\n  - Full Readable stream API: \\`.on('data' | 'end' | 'error' | 'close', cb)\\`, \\`.pipe(...)\\`, \\`.pause()\\`, \\`.resume()\\`, \\`.read()\\`, \\`.destroy()\\`, \\`.destroyed\\`\n  - \\`.socket\\` / \\`.connection\\` with \\`.remoteAddress\\`, \\`.remotePort\\`, \\`.destroy()\\`, \\`.destroySoon()\\`, \\`.destroyed\\`\n  - \\`.aborted\\`, \\`.trailers\\`\n- \\`ServerResponse\\` (Writable stream):\n  - \\`.statusCode\\`, \\`.statusMessage\\` (settable)\n  - \\`.setHeader(name, value)\\`, \\`.getHeader(name)\\`, \\`.removeHeader(name)\\`, \\`.hasHeader(name)\\`, \\`.getHeaders()\\`, \\`.getHeaderNames()\\`\n  - \\`.writeHead(status, statusMsg?, headers?)\\`\n  - \\`.write(chunk, encoding?, cb?)\\`, \\`.end(chunk?, encoding?, cb?)\\`\n  - \\`.headersSent\\`, \\`.writableEnded\\`, \\`.writableFinished\\`\n  - \\`.on('close' | 'error' | 'finish', cb)\\`\n  - \\`.flushHeaders()\\`, \\`.writeContinue()\\`, \\`.writeProcessing()\\`\n  - Chunked encoding + Content-Length auto-handling\n  - 100-continue support\n\n### Phase 2 — `node:https` server\n\nSame surface as Phase 1, plus:\n- \\`https.createServer(opts, handler)\\` where \\`opts\\` includes \\`{ key, cert, ca, passphrase, ... }\\`\n- TLS via rustls (already in perry's reqwest dependency tree)\n- SNI for multi-host setups\n- ALPN for HTTP/2 negotiation handoff to Phase 3\n\n### Phase 3 — `node:http2` server\n\nRequired for hono's HTTP/2 path and for any modern framework wanting multiplexing:\n- \\`http2.createSecureServer(opts, handler)\\`\n- \\`Http2ServerRequest\\` / \\`Http2ServerResponse\\` (similar surface to Phase 1's IncomingMessage/ServerResponse but stream-multiplexed)\n- Server push (deprioritized, web standards have moved away)\n- ALPN negotiation between HTTP/1.1 and HTTP/2 on the same port\n\n### Phase 4 — WebSocket upgrade integration\n\nPerry already has perry-ext-ws (\\`js_ws_server_new\\` + client-side too — confirmed). Phase 4 wires it into the http server:\n- \\`Server.on('upgrade', (request, socket, head) => ...)\\` event for raw upgrade handling\n- \\`@hono/node-server\\`'s \\`websocket\\` option works (uses \\`ws\\`'s \\`WebSocketServer({ noServer: true })\\` + manual upgrade dispatch)\n- Standard \\`ws\\` package's Server class works against perry's http.Server\n- HTTP/2 WebSocket (RFC 8441) — separate consideration, may defer\n\n## Architecture\n\nBuild on existing pieces where possible:\n- \\`perry-stdlib::framework::server\\` already has hyper-based HTTP/1.1 server. Reshape it from request-pull (\\`js_http_server_accept\\`) to handler-push (handler invoked with req+res handles).\n- \\`perry-ext-fastify\\` already handles GC roots for closures across the request lifecycle, async dispatch, Promise awaiting. Pattern extracts cleanly.\n- \\`perry-ext-ws\\` already has WebSocket server. Need to expose the upgrade-from-http path.\n\nModule structure proposal:\n- New crate \\`perry-ext-http-server\\` (HTTP/1.1 + HTTPS) — separate from perry-ext-http (which is client-side).\n- HTTP/2 either inside the same crate or split as \\`perry-ext-http2-server\\` depending on hyper's http2 feature footprint.\n- Well-known module flips for \\`http\\`, \\`https\\`, \\`http2\\` to route imports through the new crate.\n\nGC + concurrency considerations:\n- Each request body is buffered in Rust until the handler reads from the IncomingMessage stream. Backpressure is needed for large uploads.\n- Closures stored on Server, IncomingMessage, ServerResponse must be GC-pinned across the request lifecycle (issue #35 pattern, already solved in perry-ext-fastify).\n- Server lifetime ties to listen() — \\`process.exit()\\` should close gracefully.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\nPhase 1 MVP:\n- \\`@hono/node-server\\` works unchanged against perry-compiled programs. \\`serve({ fetch: app.fetch, port: 3000 })\\` listens on 3000, curl GET / returns hono's Response byte-for-byte. (Closes #487.)\n- Minimal Express app (\\`app.get('/', (req, res) => res.json({ok: true})); app.listen(3000)\\`) compiles + runs + responds to curl identically to Node.\n- Minimal Koa app does the same.\n- POST with JSON body parsed correctly via \\`req.on('data') / req.on('end')\\` pattern.\n\nPhase 2:\n- Same Express/Koa/hono apps work over HTTPS with self-signed cert.\n\nPhase 3:\n- \\`http2.createSecureServer\\` runs a multiplexed test program against \\`curl --http2\\`.\n\nPhase 4:\n- \\`ws\\` package's standard \\`new WebSocketServer({ server })\\` pattern works.\n- \\`@hono/node-server\\`'s websocket option passes its docs example.\n\n## Out of scope (file separately if needed)\n\n- Cluster module (\\`node:cluster\\`)\n- Worker threads HTTP support (\\`worker_threads\\` already separately implemented as perry/thread)\n- HTTP/3 / QUIC\n\n## References\n\n- @hono/node-server source: https://github.com/honojs/node-server\n- Node.js http docs: https://nodejs.org/api/http.html\n- hyper Rust crate (existing dep): https://github.com/hyperium/hyper\n- Existing perry pieces: \\`crates/perry-stdlib/src/framework/server.rs\\`, \\`crates/perry-ext-fastify/\\`, \\`crates/perry-ext-ws/\\` (server-side WS already implemented via \\`js_ws_server_new\\`)\n\nRefs #487, #421","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/PerryTS/perry/issues/577/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/PerryTS/perry/issues/577/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/opensearch-project/OpenSearch-Dashboards/issues/11713","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/opensearch-project/OpenSearch-Dashboards","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/opensearch-project/OpenSearch-Dashboards/issues/11713/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/opensearch-project/OpenSearc